            "creation_date": 1396526588,
            "body": "<p>You're probably missing some dependant library. In Eclipse you can look inside the jar file from project explorer and verify that there is a package 'org.apache.axis.client' and it contains class AxisClient. <\/p>\n\n<p>(If you're not in Eclipse then otherwise you can just unpack your jar and see that the class is there - many possibilities for that, you can even rename the jar into zip and unpack it).<\/p>\n\n<p>If the class file is in place, you're still missing it from classpath.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 22837133,
            "question_id": 22836857
        },
        {
